This paper deals with the security and privacy of the Tor network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the design and implementation of a browser extension, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves monitoring and analyzing network traffic, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
